description: Channeling my inner tomato girl this summer ( + dressing for the life I don’t have) 🍅 The #tomatogirlaesthetic emerged on TikTok in May 2023 and championed a life of reading poetry on the beaches of capri or marbella and making caprese salad from the tomatoes in your garden — all while embracing vintage sundresses, delicate gold jewellery, light linen sets, and headscarves. Data time: the trend is up +455% in views on TikTok since May 2023 and is watched by 4M people in the past month. Niche items associated with the trend are also up in searches on google — for example, the silk headscarf has seen a 22% increase in the past month. 79% of the viewers are Gen-Z (aged 18-25) and the majority are from the USA, South Africa, and Ireland. While the title of this trend/aesthetic is a bit goofy, calling it “vintage summer southern european outfits” is less catchy. In my research, I found that the best inspo came from 90s fashion photoshoots with Chrissy Turlington, Naomi Campbell, Monica Bellucci, and Beverly Peele (Vogue 1992 Postcard from Portofino is THEE aesthetic) as well as Nick DeWolf’s 70s streetstyle fashion photography.  #summeraesthetic #moodboard #romcomcore #fashiontrends #dataanalytics #romcom #outfits #ootd #streetstyle #eurosummer #eurocore #outfitoftheday #outfits #modest #tomatogirl #tomatogirloutfit #tomatogirlaesthetic #italyoutfits #vintage #retro #retrofashion #90sfashion

description: 🍅Tomato girl 🍅 Um visual bem good vibes, que mulheres jovens exploram mais sua beleza natural, romântica e com estilo livre. A maioria dos looks são compostos por estampas florais, vestidos esvoaçantes-que podem, ou não, vir estampados e com desenhos de corações. Além de peças com mangas bufantes, tecido volumoso com babados na altura do busto e fendas na perna. Óculos escuros, sapatilhas, lenços de cabeça e ecobags também são usados para compor o estilo. Já a maquiagem é algo bem sutil, como uma base de cobertura baixa, no olhar, o uso de rímel e delineador é bem-vindo, mas nada com extravagância. Um blush rosa e avermelhado, aparentando um leve bronzeado. E o cabelo segue a mesma linha de naturalidade, sendo bem comum deixar as madeixas onduladas. Por aqui 🇧🇷 ainda curtimos um friozinho,  mas já podemos nos preparar e ficar nesse verão lindo que vai pintar por aí! #fashion #moda #clothes #tomatogirl #tendências #primaveraverão2024

accumulated_text: Ginger ale gang rise up As a flight attendant: this is so typically, I’m always amazed that so many passengers like to drink tomato juice, they order it all the time. omg i have found my people. I LOVE TOMATO JUICE ON THE PLANE Fun fact due to altitude foods become more bland. Airplane food contains more salt hence why we tend to like tomato juice during a flight Chilled tomato juice with a splash of lemon juice, worcester sauce, tabacso sauce + pepper dusted on top 👌 apple juice only on the plane the perception of taste changes due to altitude and pressure If you travel to Canada get a Caesar it’s better than tomato juice and get them to make it into a cocktail for you Le goût est influencé par pleins de facteurs : ouïe, l’altitude, la pressurisation,… et dans un avion ça nous rend moins sensible à l’acidité ! Some kid threw up his tomato juice on the plane. Smell was horrendous Tomatoes help you absorb oxygen ✈️ I thought that was a silica gel packet My acid reflux can never😭 Add vodka 🥰 It’s the white noise- makes you taste umami more and sweet and salty less. Is that powdered vodka I THOUGHT I WAS THE ONLY ONE! It is ritual for me to drink tomato juice every flight! I do the SAME thing! I never drink tomato juice but I crave it every time I’m on a plane! OMGGGGG SAME 😭😭😭 This reminds me so much of my dad who passed away in March… Whatever with the travel, he would order tomato juice, salt, and pepper packets 🥹🥹 La base, un peu de sel un peu de poivre = un régal Every meals in plane taste better Cranberry juice is my go to Tomato juice is always a vibe 🍅 Needs vodka Seasoned V8 girl through and through Cran Apple gang wya Since your taste buds are blunted during a flight, tomato juice, which some might normally find too acidy, salty, become more pallatable and tasty that or ginger ale..something I would never get in real life hahaha Same here! description: Tomatini A few weeks ago I made the Tomato Girl Margarita as a nod to the Tomato Girl Summer trend from last year. And it made me want to try more tomato cocktails…that aren’t a Bloody Mary. Andwhen I saw a @Tamsin 🕊 make a Tomatini using La Petite Maison’s recipe, I knew I had to try it.  While the Tomato Margarita is for the Tomato Girl, the Tomatini is for the Tomato Lady. That elegant creature that graces the aperitivo hour in white linen, effortlessly coifed hair, enormous sunglasses and a straw bag. She orders only seasonal produce and has the perfect recipe for any occasion. She always brings dessert and makes the best evening espresso. If fact she is more than just the Tomato Lady, she is the Tomato Queen and this, this is her Martin-i.  Ingredients: - 4 cherry tomatoes  - 1 1/2 oz vodka - 1 oz white balsamic glaze - 3/4 oz simple syrup Muddle cherry tomatoes in a shaker. Add white balsamic glaze (must be glaze not vinegar), simple syrup, vodka and ice. Shake well until the tin is frosted. Double strain over a cocktail glass and garnish with a pinch of flaky salt, fresh cracked pepper and a spring of basil. #drinksmarternotharder #tomatogirlsummer #tomato #tomatini #vodka #whitebalsamic #martini

description: It’s always Tomato Girl Summer at the Sky House! 🍅✨ I only have a few green tomatoes on my backyard vines right now, but the farmers markets are starting to get their big beautiful heirlooms and sweet tiny tomato treats! In my eyes, summer is now officially in full swing! 🌞 As a kid, growing up in the agricultural Central Valley, we knew it was peak summer when the corners of the highway on-ramps would be scattered with Roma tomatoes from the tomato trucks losing a few as they took their wide turns. 🍅 To this day, seeing a tomato truck with a huge load of red tomatoes makes my heart so happy! 🥰 Who else is a tomato super fan?! 🤩 Hear me out, tomato girl summer is not just for the girlies, it’s for everyone! This is the season to eat aaaalll the tomatoes with reckless abandon! 😋 If you’ve ever pulled a sub-par, out-of-season tomato from your burger, or picked around the tomatoes in your salad, no more! 😂 Now is our time to shine! ✨ Tomato lovers unite! 😍🍅❤️✨ . . . #tomatogirlsummer #tomatoseason #tomatolover #tomatoes #skyhousekitchen

description: aha tamato😋😋😋 #tiktok #video #viraltiktok #myangelbaby #সন্তান #tomato

Tomato season baby 🍅🍸🌱 This is a trust the process kinda recipe but I highly recommend trying out The Tomatini this Fall! If you like dirty martinis, caesars or bloody marys you’re going to be obsessed with this. Being Italian end of summer always meant tomato sauce season and making this cocktail definitely brought back all those memories 🇮🇹 Send this to someone who needs to try this!  The Tomatini: 🍅 Grate and mash 2 tomatoes through a strainer. To remove the seeds, skin and excess pulp  🍅 In a cocktail shaker add 2oz vodka 🍅 0.5oz Vermouth  🍅 0.5oz of olive brine 🍅 1.5oz of the strained tomato juice  🍅 shake & pour in to a martini glass. You can also batch this without the ice and let it sit for an even fuller taste. Also don’t forget to chill your martini glass like I did 😂 🍅 Garnish with a mini vine tomato, basil leaf and a few drops of olive oil  #tomatini #savorycocktails #cocktailsathome #cocktailideas #tomatococktail #fallcocktails #martini #dirtymartini #tomatoseason #verydemure

description: Tomato head  #skintone

Tomato Egg Ingredients * 4 eggs * Salt to taste * Neutral oil * 2 scallions(sliced) * 3-4 tomatoes(cut into chunks) * 2 tbsp water * 1 tsp soy sauce * 2 tsp oyster sauce * 2 tsp sugar * 2 tbsp ketchup * 1/4 tsp white pepper * 1/4 tsp msg * 1 tsp sesame oil Instructions 1. Prep ingredients by slicing scallions and cutting tomatoes into chunks.  2. Whisk eggs and season with a pinch of salt.  3. Heat 3 tbsp of oil in a wok on medium high heat. Pour eggs and scramble and once the eggs are set but are still slightly runny, set it aside(30-45 seconds). 4. Add 2 tbsp oil to the same wok and sauté the white portion of scallions(30 seconds). 5. Once fragrant, add the tomatoes and a splash of water.  6. Let that simmer and once the tomatoes become soft and release their juices, add soy sauce, oyster sauce, sugar, ketchup, white pepper, and msg. 7. Let that simmer and once thickened, incorporate the scrambled eggs. 8. Finish with a little sesame oil and garnish with the green portion of scallions. #30minutemeals #tomatoegg #tomatoeggstir-fry #tomatoeggstirfry #recipe #cooking #food #stir-fry #stirfry #recipevideo #cookingvideo #foodvideo #recipetutorial #cookingtutorial #easyrecipe #easyrecipes #easyrecipeideas #quickrecipe #quickrecipes #quickrecipeideas #tomato #egg #asianfood #comfortfood #cookingathome
